LABEL: rubber cement
Additional info: Solvents typically used include acetone, hexane, heptane or toluene.
Text Definition: A drying adhesive made from elastic polymers mixed in a solvent.

LABEL: wallpaper paste
Text Definition: An adhesive used to fix wallpaper to walls

LABEL: permanent hair dye
Text Definition: A coloring agent used to permanently alter hair color.

LABEL: pharmaceutical ink
Text Definition: An ingestible form of water based ink used to print on pill medications.

LABEL: gel ink
Text Definition: A high viscosity, opaque ink used in gel pens.

LABEL: soy ink
Text Definition: A slow drying ink made from refined soybean oil.

LABEL: aqueous inkjet printer ink
Text Definition: A coloring agent used to deposit color onto a substrate via inkjet printer.

LABEL: emissions from gasoline combustion
Text Definition: A mixture of gases and particles produced from the combustion of petroleum fuels in vehicles.
